#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:60
msgid "pytest.raises"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:62
msgid "**Tutorial**: :ref:`assertraises`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:1
msgid ""
"Assert that a code block/function call raises ``expected_exception`` or "
"raise a failure exception otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:4
msgid ""
"If specified, a string containing a regular expression, or a regular "
"expression object, that is tested against the string representation of the "
"exception using ``re.search``. To match a literal string that may contain "
"`special characters`__, the pattern can first be escaped with ``re."
"escape``.  (This is only used when ``pytest.raises`` is used as a context "
"manager, and passed through to the function otherwise. When using ``pytest."
"raises`` as a function, you can use: ``pytest.raises(Exc, func, "
"match=\"passed on\").match(\"my pattern\")``.)  __ https://docs.python.org/3/"
"library/re.html#regular-expression-syntax"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:5
msgid ""
"If specified, a string containing a regular expression, or a regular "
"expression object, that is tested against the string representation of the "
"exception using ``re.search``. To match a literal string that may contain "
"`special characters`__, the pattern can first be escaped with ``re.escape``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:11
msgid ""
"(This is only used when ``pytest.raises`` is used as a context manager, and "
"passed through to the function otherwise. When using ``pytest.raises`` as a "
"function, you can use: ``pytest.raises(Exc, func, match=\"passed on\")."
"match(\"my pattern\")``.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:20
msgid ""
"Use ``pytest.raises`` as a context manager, which will capture the exception "
"of the given type::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:23
msgid ""
">>> import pytest\n"
">>> with pytest.raises(ZeroDivisionError):\n"
"...    1/0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:27
msgid ""
"If the code block does not raise the expected exception "
"(``ZeroDivisionError`` in the example above), or no exception at all, the "
"check will fail instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:30
msgid ""
"You can also use the keyword argument ``match`` to assert that the exception "
"matches a text or regex::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:33
msgid ""
">>> with pytest.raises(ValueError, match='must be 0 or None'):\n"
"...     raise ValueError(\"value must be 0 or None\")\n"
"\n"
">>> with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=r'must be \\d+$'):\n"
"...     raise ValueError(\"value must be 42\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:39
msgid ""
"The context manager produces an :class:`ExceptionInfo` object which can be "
"used to inspect the details of the captured exception::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:42
msgid ""
">>> with pytest.raises(ValueError) as exc_info:\n"
"...     raise ValueError(\"value must be 42\")\n"
">>> assert exc_info.type is ValueError\n"
">>> assert exc_info.value.args[0] == \"value must be 42\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:49
msgid ""
"When using ``pytest.raises`` as a context manager, it's worthwhile to note "
"that normal context manager rules apply and that the exception raised *must* "
"be the final line in the scope of the context manager. Lines of code after "
"that, within the scope of the context manager will not be executed. For "
"example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:55
msgid ""
">>> value = 15\n"
">>> with pytest.raises(ValueError) as exc_info:\n"
"...     if value > 10:\n"
"...         raise ValueError(\"value must be <= 10\")\n"
"...     assert exc_info.type is ValueError  # this will not execute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:61
msgid ""
"Instead, the following approach must be taken (note the difference in "
"scope)::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:64
msgid ""
">>> with pytest.raises(ValueError) as exc_info:\n"
"...     if value > 10:\n"
"...         raise ValueError(\"value must be <= 10\")\n"
"...\n"
">>> assert exc_info.type is ValueError"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:70
msgid "**Using with** ``pytest.mark.parametrize``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:72
msgid ""
"When using :ref:`pytest.mark.parametrize ref` it is possible to parametrize "
"tests such that some runs raise an exception and others do not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:76
msgid "See :ref:`parametrizing_conditional_raising` for an example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:78
msgid "**Legacy form**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:80
msgid "It is possible to specify a callable by passing a to-be-called lambda::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:82
msgid ""
">>> raises(ZeroDivisionError, lambda: 1/0)\n"
"<ExceptionInfo ...>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:85
msgid "or you can specify an arbitrary callable with arguments::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:87
msgid ""
">>> def f(x): return 1/x\n"
"...\n"
">>> raises(ZeroDivisionError, f, 0)\n"
"<ExceptionInfo ...>\n"
">>> raises(ZeroDivisionError, f, x=0)\n"
"<ExceptionInfo ...>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:94
msgid ""
"The form above is fully supported but discouraged for new code because the "
"context manager form is regarded as more readable and less error-prone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:98
msgid ""
"Similar to caught exception objects in Python, explicitly clearing local "
"references to returned ``ExceptionInfo`` objects can help the Python "
"interpreter speed up its garbage collection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/python_api.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.python_api.raises:102
msgid ""
"Clearing those references breaks a reference cycle (``ExceptionInfo`` --> "
"caught exception --> frame stack raising the exception --> current frame "
"stack --> local variables --> ``ExceptionInfo``) which makes Python keep all "
"objects referenced from that cycle (including all local variables in the "
"current frame) alive until the next cyclic garbage collection run. More "
"detailed information can be found in the official Python documentation for :"
"ref:`the try statement <python:try>`."
msgstr ""

